{
  "stem": "444.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was-- when I was waiting-- I got out of the cell, and I stood with my hands behind, waiting for somebody to lead me out.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was a woman, a warden, and she put something in my hand.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I didn't look, but I knew something was in my hand.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "When I got out there was, like, $5.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So my dream was to get something to eat because we were fed very badly.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was only 97 pounds when I got out, and that $5 took- that's what I had to pay for the dinner.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the next day, I didn't have any money for the railroad, so I went from behind-- I didn't enter the railroad station from the front.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I went from behind and went into the-- the-- the-- wagon.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so I went to the town of Cracow.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were two places where we had to go out.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And when I came to the town Cracow, I was still without any money.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was a time when Hitler called all the [SPEAKING GERMAN], [GERMAN], in German, back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And there was, they call it [GERMAN], bessarabiandeutsche, which means a meeting place for bessarabiandeutsche, so I joined the group.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I went with them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And for two days, I got something to eat, and I had some place to sleep.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And then, the same way, without money, I went to the town of Lublin.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But in the-- in the middle of the-- of the-- [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] of the travel, the fellow who was taking tickets came to me, and I told him I got out of prison, I didn't have any money.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "So he locked me up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He locked me up, didn't say anything.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
